Fig. 1
 represents the theoretical model proposed, with the constructs, observable variables and hypotheses of the research with the relations of influence between the constructs. The Measurement Model, formed by the observable variables of each construct, is composed of affirmations based on the literature consulted (Table 2
), as well as the constructs conceptualized in Table 1. The Structural Model, which measures the relations between the constructs, expressed in hypotheses of research, was developed based on the literature, in which the theoretical model proposes a causal relationship and influence among the constructs.
